  Locus:
    Page: 430
    Verse: 18
Tags:
  - Silence
---
Silence of the sewn-up lips is no silence. One may achieve the same result
by chopping off one's tongue, but that too would not be silence. He is
silent who, having the capacity to speak, utters no idle word.
